I decided to buy nothing but tech products with zero reviews to see if they're hidden gems or absolute disasters. From a $100 BLU phone to a sketchy gaming PC that arrived in pieces, I put everything to the test so you don't have to. Some turned out surprisingly great while others made me question my life choices.
